  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas had mixed feelings about \"The Force Awakens.\" While he appreciated the film's technical aspects and acknowledged its success, he expressed some disappointment with it creatively. In interviews, Lucas mentioned that he had provided story treatments for the sequel trilogy, but Disney decided not to use them. He also commented that \"The Force Awakens\" had too much of a \"retro\" feel and that it didn't offer enough new things, likening it to a reboot rather than a continuation of his original vision. Additionally, Lucas mentioned feeling somewhat like he was disconnected from the franchise after selling Lucasfilm to Disney. However, he was also supportive of J.J. Abrams and Kathleen Kennedy and wished them success with the new direction.",
